                    <td>
A bard holding aggro is definitely doable.  The only problem is
that it's a lot of work.  And a 3 song twist is already a lot of
work to certain people, so you'll rarely see bards hold aggro.

The best &quot;snap&quot; aggro for a bard is landing assonance and
bellow at once.  If you're in a large race illusion you can also
slam for that little extra hate bonus.

You don't &quot;need&quot; to twist 4 dots to keep aggro.  If you stand
close to the mob and melee, click in drums to do full dot
damage, you ...</td>
