                  <tr>
                    <td>

To be able to lull mobs that have a larger aggro radius than
lull itself, you must have fading memories.

The way it works is that you will run in aggro range, start
the lull song, and right before it lands you hit FM to lose
all aggro.  If done correctly, the lull will land before the mob
re-aggro's thus reducing its aggro range and preventing it
from re-aggro'ing at all.

It takes a little practice, and a lot of guts, but especially
lately with all the server-tick-aggro tricks, ...</td>
                  </tr>
                </table>
              </td>
	</tr><tr>
